flection configuration for `Field#setAccessible(true)`. I wonder if it needs `allowWrite` or `allowUnsafeAccess`. When I consider fields in the reflect-config, it seems that by default \\\"queriedFields\\\" versus \\\"fields\\\" could imply that `fields` allows introspection and access. I think that's right. It should be fine for getting a final field. There could be an issue with accessing delegate fields marked as final, though!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_U1b2zuFsBIOpZB5Sy9kOhpyH|fc_0c56a61f7d7cc3270169f750c919008195a0899845d3108ff4", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "awk 'length($0)>100{print FNR \":\" length($0) \":\" $0}' tests/src/io.opentelemetry/opentelemetry-exporter-common/1.28.0/src/test/java/io_opentelemetry/opentelemetry_exporter_common/AuthenticatorTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 700, "output": 936, "cacheRead": 24576, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26212, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777815739588, "responseId": "resp_0c56a61f7d7cc3270169f750bc0ad0819590f476c0100f3a0d"}}
